fullAddress.title: Full address
fullAddress.description: The complete address written as a string. Use of this property is recommended as it will not suffer any misunderstandings that might arise through the breaking up of an address into its component parts.

thoroughfare.title: Thoroughfare
thoroughfare.description: The name of a passage or way through from one location to another. A thoroughfare is usually a street, but it might be a waterway or some other feature.

locatorDesignator.title: Locator designator
locatorDesignator.description: A number or sequence of characters that uniquely identifies the locator within the relevant scope. In simpler terms, this is the building number, apartment number, etc.

locatorName.title: Locator name
locatorName.description: Proper noun(s) applied to the real world entity identified by the locator. The locator name could be the name of the property or complex, of the building or part of the building, or it could be the name of a room inside a building. The key difference between a locator designator and a locator name is that the latter is a proper name and is unlikely to include digits.

addressArea.title: Address area
addressArea.description: The name of a geographic area that groups addresses. This would typically be part of a city, a neighbourhood or village. Address area is not an administrative unit.

postCode.title: Post code
postCode.description: The code created and maintained for postal purposes to identify a subdivision of addresses and postal delivery points.

postName.title: Post name
postName.description: A name created and maintained for postal purposes to identify a subdivision of addresses and postal delivery points. Usually a city.

poBox.title: PO box
poBox.description: A location designator for a postal delivery point at a post office, usually a number.

adminUnitLevel1.title: Admin unit level 1
adminUnitLevel1.description: The name of the uppermost level of the address, almost always a country. ISO 3166 three character (Alpha 3) format.

adminUnitLevel2.title: Admin unit level 2
adminUnitLevel2.description: The name of a secondary level/region of the address, usually a county, state or other such area that typically encompasses several localities. Values could be a region or province, more granular than level 1.

name.title: Name
name.description: The desired name to be registered for the company

alternativeName.title: Alternative name
alternativeName.description: The second alternative for the desired name to be registered for the company if the primary name is not available

foundingDate.title: Founding date
foundingDate.description: The date of memorandum of association

industrySector.title: Industry sector
industrySector.description: The industry fields where the company will run its business. The codes are based on the Statistical classification of economic activities in the European Community, abbreviated as NACE.

shareCapital.title: Share capital
shareCapital.description: The total value of the issued shares of the company

capitalCurrency.title: Capital currency
capitalCurrency.description: The currency used for the share capital in ISO 4217 format

settlementDeposit.title: Settlement deposit
settlementDeposit.description: The amount of the deposit paid during the establishment of a company

depositCurrency.title: Deposit currency
depositCurrency.description: The currency used for the paying the settlement deposit in ISO 4217 format

settlementDate.title: Settlement date
settlementDate.description: The date on which the share deposit has been settled and available as full

countryOfResidence.title: Country of residence
countryOfResidence.description: The company's current country of the residence in the three character (Alpha-3) format if it already exists abroad
